{
 "name": "09b — RAG Evaluation",
 "nodes": [
  {
   "parameters": {
    "content": "📖 [Course documentation](https://ezponda.github.io/ai-agents-course/09b_testing_and_evaluating_ai_workflows.html)\n## Evaluating a RAG workflow\n**Goal:** Run the RAG assistant against a fixed **test dataset** (Data Table `rag_eval_cases`) — one row per case — and score it with **valid** metrics: a per-case `case_passed`, plus a separate `retrieval_hit` for the retrieval branch.\n\n### Two parts\n1. **Ingest (top):** upload the handbook once so the store is filled.\n2. **Evaluate (bottom):** trigger → map row → **two branches** (answer via the agent, retrieval via a direct vector-store query) → merge → score → metrics.\n\n⚠️ **Re-index first** (in-memory store). ⚠️ **No shared memory** (each row independent). ⚠️ `retrieval_hit` is meaningful only on rows with `expected_retrieval_contains`; read it filtered to those rows. ⚠️ Evaluation / vector-store `load` node labels vary by n8n version — verify in your UI.",
    "height": 380,
    "width": 680
   },
   "id": "22000000-0000-4000-8000-0000000000s1",
   "name": "NOTE",
   "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
   "typeVersion": 1,
   "position": [
    -1340,
    -540
   ]
  },
  {
   "parameters": {
    "formTitle": "Upload Document",
    "formDescription": "Upload a PDF or text file to create a searchable knowledge base.",
    "formFields": {
     "values": [
      {
       "fieldLabel": "Document",
       "fieldType": "file",
       "acceptFileTypes": ".pdf,.txt,.md",
       "requiredField": true
      }
     ]
    },
    "options": {
     "respondWith": "text",
     "formSubmittedText": "Document uploaded and indexed successfully! You can now open the Chat in n8n to ask questions."
    }
   },
